{"key":"processedPost-12776091","value":{"id":12776091,"first":12775413,"last":12776091,"when":1277092163,"utime":"06/21/10 06:49 AM","content":"That's the best use for popcorn.&nbsp; I use the same kettle I sterilize jars or boil grain in to make popcorn.&nbsp; Add some salt and butter and I'm ready for a good movie.<br /><br />Using it as spawn will generally lead to a higher bacteria contamination rate.&nbsp; Some of the endospores that form on popcorn are genuinely hard to kill.&nbsp; In addition, when spawned to bulk, especially straw, the large kernel size allows LOTS of mold spores to land on them, and all it takes is for the mycelium to weaken in one little spot, and the mold can take over.<br /><br />I had about a 5% failure rate with popcorn, but that's enough to get me to switch to the real thing, rye for a 0% fail rate.<br />RR","title":"Re: So is Popcorn and Cracked corn","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}